column191: participantComments:"I focused on the fact that the purple worker only deviated from going to the center tree once
column192: whereas in all of the first two trials both workers went to the center tree every time (which was the optimal solution for both of them
column193: as both going to the center tree would yield the best outcomes for each of them both individually and collectively). I was a bit confused why either would ever deviate from going to the center tree under the conditions
column194: but it seemed like they generally agreed upon the solution of going to the center tree
column195: such that deviating from it would be perceived negatively because it harms BOTH of them. "
